Do you ever feel hoplessness and void in the pit of your stomic? Like maybe your a just a pon in somone elses game of life? Like the mith of fait..is it true? Are our lifes pre-destened? Is the reason we humans have an obsession with control because we really have none? Do we strive to fill a void? A void in which we are cursed to never really control our own lives? A void in which when filled is a fake fofillment of control? Are we just marinette pupits in gods hands? Not alowed to make choice for ouself? cursed to an eternal game of chess? Being pushed acrossed the "bord of life"? Regardless what what, or who we want to be? 
 This void, where and why is it here? Why do some feel it, but others dont feel the hopless void? Can some fill it with fake ideas? Ideas of "control" of people? Politics, or government bodys who belive they control the fate of ones nation? Or in christianity, and other realigions who teach of a higher power, who dosnt control us but gives us free will? If this free will is true, then why do some say.."I knwo your gunna be great somday." Do we really want to be great? Or is it our destiny? Are we cursed to be what somone else wants? Or can we chose to be great, or not to be great. The luck, yes luck, of becoming great has high odds, stacked against us. In 200 years of being in existance only 42 people have ever had "control" of this country. Very few will really be remember. So what is to say that maybe, its decided ahead of time, in which case, what is the real point of living your life..will it just fall into place?
